Applying the product rule for the first derivative g'(x):
g'(x) = u'v + uv' = (3x^2 + 5)e^x + (x^3 + 5x)e^x;
Second derivative g''(x):
g''(x) = (3x^2 + 5)'e^x + (3x^2 + 5)e^x + (x^3 + 5x)'e^x + (x^3 + 5x)e^x = (6x)e^x + (3x^2 + 5)e^x + (3x^2 + 5)e^x + (6x)e^x + (x^3 + 5x)e^x;
Simplifying g''(x):
g''(x) = e^x(6x + 3x^2 + 5 + 3x^2 + 5 + 6x + x^3 + 5x) = e^x(6x + 6x + 5x + x^3 + 6x^2 + 10) = e^x(x^3 + 18x + 10);
Third derivative g'''(x):
g'''(x) = (x^3 + 18x + 10)'e^x + (x^3 + 18x + 10)e^x = e^x(3x^2 + 18)e^x + e^x(3x^2 + 18)e^x = 2e^x(3x^2 + 18);
Fourth derivative g''''(x):
g''''(x) = (6x^2 + 36)e^x + 2(3x^2 + 18)e^x = (6x^2 + 36)e^x + (6x^2 + 36)e^x = 2e^x(6x^2 + 36) = 2e^x(6x^2 + 36);
Fifth derivative g'''''(x):
g'''''(x) = (12x)e^x + 2(6x^2 + 36)e^x = (12x)e^x + (12x)e^x = 2e^x(12x) = 24xe^x.

The answer is: 24xe^x.

